						<summary>

						<p>Slab set up in the Janārdanadēva temple.</p>						

						<p>[Vīra-Pāṇḍyadēva], 1262 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This badly damaged record refers itself to the reign of [Pāṇḍya]dēva and mentions <hi rend="bold">mayiduna</hi> Voḍamadēva Narasiṁga-heggaḍe and others who had assembled in the palace at <hi rend="bold">Bāraha-kanyāpura.</hi> All other details are lost.</p>						

						<p>It is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka [1184] Dundubhi, Tulā [5], Sunday</hi> corresponding to 1262 A.D., October 2. The weekday was Monday.</p>						

						</summary>
					</msContents>
